ct</baseValue><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /></match></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL"><multiple><variable identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">Feedback655805922</baseValue></multiple></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition></responseProcessing><modalFeedback  identifier="Feedback655805922" outcomeIdentifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" showHide="show"><p>Make sure that your calculator is in radian mode.</p><p>Notes on converting to polar coordinates:</p><p>Take carefully account of the quadrant in which z is located. There are many possibilities of computing the principal argument Arg(z) of a given complex number z. Depending on the function you choose, you may need to add (subtract) some specific angle to the the result of your calculator to obtain Arg(z).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p></modalFeedback></assessmentItem>
